Income from investments in group enterprises
Income from investments in group enterprises comprises
the pro rata share of the group enterprises' operating
profit/loss adjusted for internal profits and losses.", "context": "The chunk discusses the accounting treatment of income from investments in group enterprises, which is presented as part of the significant accounting policies in the annual report."}
